Distinct Elements Sorter

Overview
This application processes a long list of integers and outputs the distinct elements in ascending order. Additionally,
it provides basic statistics about the input, including the total number of elements, the count of distinct elements,
and the minimum and maximum values.

Features
Input a long list of integers.
Output the list of distinct elements sorted in ascending order.
Provide basic measurement information:
Total number of elements in the source list.
Number of distinct elements.
Minimum value in the list.
Maximum value in the list.

Assumptions made:
1. The user can enter letters and special characters in addition to numbers. Letters and special characters will be
considered invalid values and omitted for further actions. The user will be informed about this.
2. It was assumed that the separator will be a comma, the user was informed about this